President Obama called Mrs. Ernestina Naadu Mills of Ghana to offer his condolences for the passing of her husband, President John Evans Atta Mills. He praised President Mills' dedication to the Ghanaian people and his efforts to strengthen the U.S.-Ghana relationship. President Obama also expressed his appreciation for the hospitality of President and Mrs. Mills during his visit to Ghana in 2009. Mrs. Mills thanked the President for recognizing her late husband's leadership and expressed her belief that the friendship between the United States and Ghana will continue.